Definition.WordDefinition:
Copenhagen \Co`pen*ha"gen\, n. [From Copenhagen, Denmark.] 1. A sweetened hot drink of spirit and beaten eggs. [Webster 1913 Suppl.]
2. A children's game in which one player is inclosed by a circle of others holding a rope. [Webster 1913 Suppl.]
Copenhagen n : the capital and largest city of Denmark; located on the island of Zealand; "Copenhagen is sometimes called the Paris of the North" [syn: {Kobenhavn}, {Danish capital}]
